Team,

 

Per our call today within the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) ran the Drop Data for the rest of the host that were on the same Proxy that Ernie2 was using.

 

We then manually deleted the Ter 2 (SQLite) DBs from the NEA FSSA path as well as the Proxy host FSAA folder path.

 

Ram the following jobs

Jobs > Z.Sandbox > FS_DropTables  << for only the 3. Drop FSDLP Tables

Jobs > FileSystem > 3.Prep > 0-Create Schema

 

Kicked of Zero level SDD scans for the host in question until we had all Successful.

 

Steven will re-increase the scan depth per his discretion and note any issues between the Tuesday and Thursday scans.

 

Please let me know how the next set of scans complete.

 

Again, thank You for your time.

 

@Nicholas Zimmer​  any additional details you would like on this follow up email?

 

Thanks for the back up on this case and call today to you and @Tay Caliguiri​
